Following [JFrog announcement about sunsetting JCenter](https://jfrog.com/blog/into-the-sunset-bintray-jcenter-gocenter-and-chartcenter/), `maoni` and all the default callback implementations are now available on Maven Central. See https://search.maven.org/artifact/org.rm3l/maoni.
So importing `maoni` should be straightforward. Add this to your `build.gradle` file:
```gradle
  repositories {
      //...
      mavenCentral()
  }

  dependencies {
    // ...
    implementation 'org.rm3l:maoni:9.0.0@aar'
  }
```
